# Interactive Learning Environment - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# DO NOT commit the .env file to version control

# ==========================================
# FIREBASE CONFIGURATION
# ==========================================
# Get these values from your Firebase Console:
# https://console.firebase.google.com/
#
# 1. Go to Project Settings
# 2. Scroll to "Your apps" section
# 3. Click on your web app (or create one)
# 4. Copy the config values

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://your_project_id-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# ==========================================
# ADMIN CREDENTIALS
# ==========================================
# Set a secure username and password for teacher login
# These credentials are used in AdminLoginModal.jsx

VITE_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=your_secure_password_here

# ==========================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES
# ==========================================
#
# 1. NEVER commit the .env file to Git
#    - It's already in .gitignore
#    - Contains sensitive credentials
#
# 2. For production:
#    - Use a strong admin password (minimum 12 characters)
#    - Consider using a password manager
#    - Rotate credentials regularly
#
# 3. Firebase Security Rules:
#    - Make sure to configure Firebase Realtime Database rules
#    - Recommended rules for production:
#      {
#        "rules": {
#          "quizzes": {
#            ".read": "auth != null || data.exists()",
#            ".write": "auth != null"
#          },
#          "game_sessions": {
#            ".read": "data.exists()",
#            ".write": "data.exists()"
#          }
#        }
#      }
#
# 4. Environment-specific configs:
#    - Use different Firebase projects for dev/staging/production
#    - Create separate .env files: .env.development, .env.production
#
# ==========================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==========================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Get Firebase credentials:
#    - Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or use existing
#    - Enable Realtime Database
#    - Copy configuration values
#
# 3. Set admin credentials:
#    - Choose secure username and password
#    - Fill in VITE_ADMIN_USERNAME and VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD
#
# 4. Save the file and restart dev server:
#    npm run dev
#
# ==========================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ==========================================
#
# Issue: "Firebase not initialized"
# Solution: Verify all VITE_FIREBASE_* variables are set correctly
#
# Issue: "Admin login fails"
# Solution: Check VITE_ADMIN_USERNAME and VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD match your input
#
# Issue: "Cannot connect to database"
# Solution: Verify VITE_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL is correct and database exists
#
# Issue: "Permission denied" errors
# Solution: Check Firebase Realtime Database security rules
#
